A '''high-voltage shore connection (HVSC)''' is connection used to connect ships to the main grid, shutting engine of the ship and reducing carbon emissions.<ref name="upc.edu">https://upcommons.upc.edu/bitstream/handle/2117/88596/120286_00%20FNB-TFGdef3.pdf?sequence=1&isAllowed=y</ref> 

The ship can use electric power for its consumption of energy. They are mostly used in the [[cruise ships]] which dock for longer time and hence save energy.<ref name="upc.edu"/>

