'''''S''-Adenosylmethioninamine''' ('''decarboxylated [[S-Adenosyl methionine|''S''-adenosyl methionine]]''') is a [[Substrate (biochemistry)|substrate]] that is involved in the biosynthesis of [[polyamines]] including [[spermidine]], [[spermine]], and [[thermospermine]].<ref name="takahashi">{{cite journal|last=Takahashi|first=Taku|first2=Jun-Ichi|last2=Kakehi |date=2009-10-13|title=Polyamines: Ubiquitous polycations with unique roles in growth and stress responses|journal=[[Annals of Botany]]|volume=105|issue=1|pages=1–6|doi=10.1093/aob/mcp259|pmc=2794062}}</ref> 

